Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria), mild hypoglycemia, and low total CO₂ suggesting possible metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, consistent with nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and assessment for underlying metabolic or diabetic disorders.
